Det ser ud til, at du √∏nsker en frontend, der matcher det design, vi talte om tidligere. Her er en opdateret version af `index.html` med en mere brugervenlig og centreret styling, s√• du kan l√¶gge den direkte i GitHub og bruge med Netlify:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="da">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Selfie App</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #333;
    }
    select, button {
      padding: 10px;
      font-size: 16px;
      margin: 10px;
    }
    video, canvas {
      margin-top: 20px;
      border: 2px solid #ccc;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background-color: #000;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>üì∏ Selfie App</h1>
  <label for="timer">‚è≥ V√¶lg timer:</label>
  <select id="timer">
    <option value="3">3 sekunder</option>
    <option value="5">5 sekunder</option>
    <option value="10">10 sekunder</option>
  </select>
  <button onclick="takeSelfie()">Tag Selfie</button>
  <br>
  <video id="video" width="400" autoplay></video>
  <canvas id="canvas" width="400" height="300" style="display:none;"></canvas>

  <script>
    const video = document.getElementById('video');
    const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');
    const context = canvas.getContext('2d');

    navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ video: true }).then(stream => {
      video.srcObject = stream;
    });

    function takeSelfie() {
      const delay = parseInt(document.getElementById('timer').value) * 1000;
      setTimeout(() => {
        context.drawImage(video, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
        const imgData = canvas.toDataURL('image/png');
        uploadToDrive(imgData);
      }, delay);
    }

    function uploadToDrive(imgData) {
      // Google Drive API integration kommer her
      alert("Billede taget! Upload til Google Drive skal implementeres.");
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

Denne version vil se mere p√¶n og centreret ud, n√•r du √•bner den i browseren. L√¶g den som `index.html` i dit GitHub-repo, s√• Netlify kan hoste den.
